Yes, you can.

```
{% set myVar = title | lower  %}
{% set myVar = title | lower + var2 | upper %}
{% set myVar = (title | lower  + var2) | trim %}
...
{% for item in items | sort(false, true)  %}
&lt;a href=&quot;{{ item.url | url }}&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;{{ item.title | lower}}&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
{% endfor %}
```
The `lower`, `upper` and `trim` filters are applyed to number/string vars. They cann&#39;t be applyed for some array (or object).
On the another side, the `sort`-filter expects an array as input. 

The filter &quot;type&quot; is obvious by its description in [docs](https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/templating.html#sort-arr-reverse-casesens-attr).

